<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>CfP | Christine Bauer</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/tag/cfp/</link><atom:link href="https://chbeu.github.io/tag/cfp/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>CfP</description><generator>Wowchemy (https://wowchemy.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>© 2023 Christine Bauer</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 24 Apr 2022 18:00:06 +0200</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://chbeu.github.io/media/sharing.png</url><title>CfP</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/tag/cfp/</link></image><item><title>Special Issue 'Perspectives on Recommender Systems Evaluation' @ TORS</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220424_si_tors/</link><pubDate>Sun, 24 Apr 2022 18:00:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220424_si_tors/</guid><description>&lt;p>Together with &lt;a href="https://evazangerle.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eva Zangerle&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://www.alansaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alan Said&lt;/a>, I am Guest Editor of the first special issue of the new journal &lt;a href="https://dl.acm.org/journal/tors/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ACM Transactions on Recommender Systems&lt;/a>: &amp;lsquo;Perspectives on Recommender Systems Evaluation&amp;rsquo;. The &lt;a href="TORS-CfP-SI-Evaluation.pdf">Call for Papers&lt;/a> and the submission details are already available. The deadline is &lt;em>&lt;strong>30 November 2022&lt;/strong>&lt;/em>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Keep in mind, that we also organize a workshop about this topic: &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PERSPECTIVES 2022&lt;/a> (which will be collocated with &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Co-Chair of PERSPECTIVES 2022</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</link><pubDate>Thu, 14 Apr 2022 17:35:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</guid><description>&lt;p>The workshop &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems&lt;/a> is back at &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>. I am happy to co-chair this workshop together with &lt;a href="https://evazangerle.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eva Zangerle&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://www.alansaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alan Said&lt;/a>. The &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/#cfp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Call for Papers&lt;/a> and the submission details are already available at the workshop website.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Co-editing research topic on Human Issues in Recommender Systems</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-08-16-co-editing-research-topic-on-human-issues-in-recommender-systems/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Aug 2021 12:04:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-08-16-co-editing-research-topic-on-human-issues-in-recommender-systems/</guid><description>&lt;p>I&amp;rsquo;m happy to announce that I&amp;rsquo;m co-editing with &lt;a href="https://www.bruceferwerda.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bruce Ferwerda&lt;/a> a so-called research topic in &lt;a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/big-data/sections/recommender-systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Frontiers in Big Data (Recommender Systems)&lt;/a> on &lt;a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/research-topics/23412/human-issues-in-recommender-systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Human Issues in Recommender Systems&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For more information, see &lt;a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/research-topics/23412/human-issues-in-recommender-systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.frontiersin.org/research-topics/23412/human-issues-in-recommender-systems&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>